                            <comment id="74223" author="neman" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2011 23:54:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After some examination looks to me that the String PEOPLE_SEARCH_URL in class ProfileTemplate in the package org.springframework.social.linkedin.api.impl is the problem.&lt;br/&gt;
Should be &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://api.linkedin.com/v1/people-search:(people:(id,first-name,last-name,headline,industry,site-standard-profile-request,public-profile-url,picture-url,summary,api-standard-profile-request))?&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://api.linkedin.com/v1/people-search:(people:(id,first-name,last-name,headline,industry,site-standard-profile-request,public-profile-url,picture-url,summary,api-standard-profile-request))?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
{keywords}
{&amp;amp;first-name}{&amp;amp;last-name}{&amp;amp;company-name}{&amp;amp;current-company}{&amp;amp;title}{&amp;amp;current-title}{&amp;amp;school-name}{&amp;amp;current-school}{&amp;amp;country-code}{&amp;amp;postal-code}{&amp;amp;distance}{&amp;amp;start}{&amp;amp;count}{&amp;amp;sort}&lt;br/&gt;
instead of&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://api.linkedin.com/v1/people-search:(people:(id,first-name,last-name,headline,industry,site-standard-profile-request,public-profile-url,picture-url,summary,api-standard-profile-request))?{&amp;amp;keywords}&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://api.linkedin.com/v1/people-search:(people:(id,first-name,last-name,headline,industry,site-standard-profile-request,public-profile-url,picture-url,summary,api-standard-profile-request))?{&amp;amp;keywords}&lt;/a&gt;{&amp;amp;first-name}
{&amp;amp;last-name}
{&amp;amp;company-name}
&lt;p&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/p&gt;
{current-company}
{&amp;amp;title}
{&amp;amp;current-title}
{&amp;amp;school-name}
{&amp;amp;current-school}
{&amp;amp;country-code}
{&amp;amp;postal-code}
{&amp;amp;distance}
{&amp;amp;start}
{&amp;amp;count}
{&amp;amp;sort}</comment>
                            <comment id="74377" author="habuma" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2012 08:36:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As noted in the referenced forum thread, the real problem here is that SearchParameters.Sort.RECOMMENDORS should be SearchParameters.Sort.RECOMMENDERS. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The extra &amp;amp;&apos;s are of concern, but shouldn&apos;t prevent it from working. Fixing the problem by removing the ampersand before &quot;keywords&quot; as suggested will not really fix the problem, as there will still be an extra ampersand before some other parameter if there are no keywords specified. The problem is in how parameter expansion works. While correcting the RECOMMENDERS problem, I&apos;ll also be seeking a solution that eliminates the extra ampersands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="74390" author="habuma" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2012 11:34:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve fixed both the core problem (RECOMMENDORS) as well as adjusted the parameter expansion routine to not place extra ampersands. This should address this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I&apos;m not a big fan of how the parameter expansion works and will likely revisit it to make it more solid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
